        "subtitle": "Proven Steel, Clean Lines, Great Value",
        "intro_content": "<p>The <strong>Xinzuo X020 Pin Series</strong> delivers the performance of Xinzuo’s acclaimed <strong>10Cr15CoMoV steel</strong> — the same core found in their premium Damascus lines — in a clean <strong>3-layer composite construction</strong> at <strong>60 HRC</strong>. Without the Damascus cladding, these blades offer the same cutting edge at a more accessible price point. Warm <strong>olive wood handles</strong> give each knife a natural, Mediterranean character and a comfortable grip. With 14 knife types spanning paring, utility, santoku, chef, nakiri, boning, cleaver, and bread knives, the Pin Series is one of the most complete mid-premium ranges Xinzuo offers. For Australian cooks who value substance over flash, the Pin Series proves that you don’t need decorative layers to get a genuinely excellent blade — just outstanding steel and honest craftsmanship.</p>",
