      "settings": {
        "heading": "Why choose 3-layer composite over Damascus",
        "content": "<p>The Pin Series uses the same <strong>10Cr15CoMoV steel</strong> found in Xinzuo’s premium Damascus knives. Learn how this steel compares to VG10. <a href=\"/blogs/news/vg10-steel-vs-10cr15comov-guide\">VG10 vs 10Cr15CoMoV compared</a></p><p>Understand the <strong>san-mai (3-layer) construction</strong> method and why it delivers excellent toughness alongside a hard cutting edge. <a href=\"/blogs/news/san-mai-construction-guide\">San-mai knife guide</a></p><p>New to quality kitchen knives? Our beginner guide covers blade types, steel grades, and what to look for in your first serious knife. <a href=\"/blogs/news/beginner-kitchen-knife-buying-guide\">Beginner knife buying guide</a></p><p>Find the best kitchen knives at every price point, from entry-level to professional grade. <a href=\"/blogs/news/best-kitchen-knives-every-budget\">Best knives for every budget</a></p><p>Keep your Pin Series knife razor-sharp with a proper sharpening routine — 10Cr steel responds beautifully to a whetstone. <a href=\"/blogs/news/how-to-sharpen-knives-whetstone\">How to sharpen on a whetstone</a></p><p>Ready for Damascus? The <strong>Lan Series</strong> uses the same 10Cr15CoMoV core wrapped in 67 layers of Damascus steel. <a href=\"/collections/xinzuo-lan-series-knives\">Shop the Lan Series</a></p>",
